    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "interesting. i noticed you mentioned caucasian beauty using words like \"classic standard\" and \"symmetrical features\" while describing other groups with more specific/physical traits. some people in the industry argue that these \"classic\" Western standards are actually the benchmark that everyone else is trying to move toward. do you think there's actually a \"true\" global ideal that most people are subconsciously aiming for, even if they're in different ethnic groups?",
